content: SHEILA!!!! This is my Mom's essence in a photo, captured sometime in the 90's at our old home in Eagle Rock. If you've ever been to our home you already know -- you will never forget my mom's hospitality! Her smile *literally* sparkles and her joy is just infectious. She is kind, warm, so full of life and God's love. She makes everyone feel safe, comfortable and welcome. I get my creative mind from this woman and a bit of her theatrics may have rubbed off on me too üòÇ Having two headstrong young women in one home made for lots of drama, but to any moms and daughters going through it right now -- push through. You'll meet again as adults and reach a whole new understanding of each other. @moneesmom you are my rock, my hero, my inspiration and my motivation. The world would be a better place if I could become a little more like you everyday ‚ú®

content: "I am the men who can." ‚òÑÔ∏èMight be my favorite line from Wonder Woman but it's hard to choose because it's THAT GOOD. The lady has a ‚ù§Ô∏è of freaking gold. Tender AND tough, she kicks ass without compromising her femininity. She's fiercely independent and still loves her man. She's not in it for the shine and celebrates her team. She loves mankind unconditionally and seeks light in darkness. Gal Gadot - thank you for embodying this badass hero I've been waiting for all my life. Gadot also wore flats to her premiere soooo def a hero in real life too! WW happens to be the biggest, most expensive action movie ever entrusted to a female director - the brilliant Patty Jenkins. She's making it rain all over the skeptical boys club that is Hollywood with that loooonng box office üí∞ as we speak. Media MATTERS - it shapes how we perceive our potential in this society. If we keep making movies like this, the world isn't ready for the next generation of lil Amazonian wonder women. #WonderWoman #NoManHating #JustGirlPower
